{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_bravo_ver01/data/sn86090383/00175034754/1908032001/0261.xml":{"full_text":"flri\nr\ni\nr\nIS\nVOL VI NO 207\nThe above statement is correct\nTucker Royall Cashier\nThe First\nImpression\nIS LIKE LAMM TAILORING\nLasting\nLAMM Clothes are Built\nYou Not the Other Fellow\nLAMM Clothes will give you So\nciety Prestige\nLAMM Clothes are backed by a\ngiltedge guarantee 500 patterns\nwill be shown with pleasure at\ntheir local agency\nrj 4 atiLBMr Mat n\nDAVI PORTER\nTAILORS\nYour Suits Clasncd With Care\nTo Earn a Little To Spend a Little Less\nAnd Invest the Balance in\nREAL ESTATE\nIN CITV OR COUNTY\nProperty\nIs the surest way to provide a competency and perhaps build a fortune\nReal estate is the best investment because it is secure and because the\nvalues are bound to go up The cheap lands of this section will not\nlong remain cheap lands\nSee me about the proposition I can start you right and show you the\nway to save\nsaveP H Hushes\nRants and Real Estate and Fire Insurance\nOffice in Robinson Bank Bldg\nThe Bank Habit\nPossibly you who read this have never kept a bank account If not let\nus suggest that you try the exprimenL Aside from the fact that your\nmoney will be safe from fire and theft such a habit tends to thrift\neconomy discipline and a general understanding of business principles\nall of which are essential to success It also affords a convenient\nmethod for the payment of bills and as the checks are always pre\nserved and returned to you they serve as receipts for the amount paid\nRobinson Bros\nEstablished 1881\nBank\nUnincorporated\nThere Is Nothing\nJn which delay is so dangerous as in Eye troubles when you\nconsider that you can get along fairly well without any sense\nexcept sight you will understand how important it is to take\nno chances with it\nOur business is to tell you when you need glasses We have\nthe proper means of finding out\nM FOLANDE\nJEWELER AND OPTICIAN\nSam Rollins\nAll Kinds of HAULING\nWill move jour Furniture and\nHousehold Goods by the load or contract Latest improved Piano\nTrucV for moving pianos Prompt service reasorable rates\nOffice Ehone 109 Sam RoIlfltS Res Phone 457\nv v isW j\nSpecial to theHerald\nNew York March 20 The annual\nreport of the United States Steel com\npany shows that the company had an\nexcellent year in the year just closed\nThe gross receipts are shown to have\nbeen 757000000 and the operating\nexpenses 565000000 The forecast\nsays the business outlook for the com\npany is excellent The trade Is con\nstantly Increasing A pension fund of\n1000000 was set aside for the em\nployes of the company\nWILL PREVENT DUEL\nBetween General Fock and Colonel\nGorbatovsky\nSpecial to the Herald\nLondon March 20 The Russian\nwar minister has decided to forbid the\nduel between General Fock and Col\nonel Gorbatovsky because Fock held\na higher command and is not respon\nsible to Gorbatovsky for anything he\nmay have said It Is now thought\nGeneral Smirnoff may recover from\nthe wounds received in a duel with\nGeneral Fock recently\nMITCHELL HAS FINISHED\nHis Task as Head of the Miners\nUnion and Steps Down and Out\nToday Says GoodBye\nSpecial to the Herald\nIndianapolis Ind March 20 John\nMitchell presided today for the last\ntime as president of the miners or\nganization and when the convention\nadjourned today he stepped down and\nout His farewell address to the del\negates plead for united action A re\nception was given him afterwards\nTears rolled down his cheeks as he\nbid the delegates goodbye\nJEWS WERE ARRESTED\nIn Russia While Holding Peaceful As\nsembly Delegates Tortured\nSpecial to the Herald\nBerlin March 20 For assembling\npeacefully at CharUoff Russia to dis\ncuss their race condition under Mus\ncovite rule sixtytwo delegates repre\nsenting a Jewish organization of na\ntional scope have been arrested and\nfrightfully tortured and are still im\nprisoned without trial and without\nany specific charges being placed\nagainst them\nTroops with fixed bajonets seized\nall delegates In tiie hall and dragged\nthem to prison brutally mistreating\nthem When they were in prison they\nwere placed In chains\nA Tariff Commission\nSpecial to the Herald\nWashington D C March 20 Sen\nator LaFollette today introduced a\nbill providing for the appointment of\na tariff commission He announced\nthat he would speak on the measure\nIn the near future\nPALESTINE DAILY HERALD\nPALESTINE TEXAS FRIDAY AFTERNOON HARCH 20 1908\nTRAGEDY HIGH LIFE TWO KILIBIN WRECK\nProminent Man of Milwaukee Killed International and Great Northern Ex\nHis Wife and Then Fired Two\nShots Into His Own Breast\nSpecial to the Herald\nMilwaukee Wis March 20 George\nWilloughby one of the leading busi\nness men of this city shot and killed\nhis wife and then fired two shots Into\nhis own breast last night He is\nthought to be dying He confessed to\nthe police that he murdered his wife\nbecause he was infatuated with an\nother woman whom he had been sup\nporting for the past four years Wil\nloughby and his wife were both prom\ninent church workers They attended\nservices last night and on returning\nhome quarreled after retiring After\nhis wife fell asleep Willoughby chlo\nroformed her and then shot her caus\ning instant death He then shot him\nself piercing the lungs He dragged\nhimself to the basement door which\nhe opened with the intention of mak\ning it appear that burglars had com\nmitted the deed He then hid his re\nvolver and returned upstairs and tel\nephoned for a doctor The police\nafter working on the burglary theory\nfor a time finally secured a full con\nfession from Willoughby\nBIG SIEEL COMPANY\nDid Enormous Business Last Year\nMillion Dollar Pension Fund Set\nAside For Employes\ncursion Train Was Wrecked\nNear Pearsall\nSan Antonio Texas March 19 The\njlives of three hundred Kansas and\nOklahoma homeseekers en route to\nLas Patinas Mexico were endanger\ned when the second section of the In\nternational and Great Northern pas\nsenger train went Into the ditch four\niplles south of Pearsall this after\nnoon at 130 oclock Two trainmen\nwere killed six persons badly injured\nand many persons slightly Injured\nThe engine broke loose from the train\nand the craw escaped unhurt The\ndejad are\nV V H Myers baggageman residing\nat 2018 West Commerce street San\nAntonio\niiU E McEIroy lineman of Western\nUnion residing at 912 Buenavista\nstreet San Antonio\nThe injured\nWalter Carevon conductor SaA An\ntonio shoulder broken\nSW H Hopper Dowe Okla badly\nbruised and Internally injured\nJ3rakeman Webb San Antonio arm\nbadly bruised\nVV J Patterson Colllnsvllle Ok\nba f bruise over left eye\nTirs R Ettman Aloon Kan head\nbruised\nL D Russell Pittsburg Pa right\nleg crushed\nJSeven other passengers were slight\nIylinjured but they proceeded on the\njourney to Mexico and their names\ncould not be learned\nThe train consisted of twelve coach\nes After the engine had passed over\na section of the track the rail spread\nderailing the tender The engine then\nbroke loose and the two baggage cars\nwere telescoped with the tender\nt Five of the coaches all sleepers\nleffjthe track The train was running\nsofast that the tender and the two\ntelescoped cars were thrown clear off\ni rlght of way Fortunately all ot\nth Tslpepers remained upright An\nother train was run from Laredo and\nthe passengers transferred and pro\nceeded on their journey Those who\nwere Injured were brought to San An\ntonio and placed In the hospital\nBaggageman Myers one of the\ndead was instantly killed being bad\nly mashed He was 24 years old and\nunmarried He resided with his uncle\nSamuel E Myers an International and\nGreat Northern conductor\nMcEIroy lived several hours after\nthe wreck but died before he reached\nthe hospital in this city The train\nleft here this morning at 10 oclock\nand was heavily loaded with passen\ngers This is the second wreck of an\nexcursion train south on the Interna\ntional and Great Northern this month\nthe Gates excursion going into the\nditch about two weeks ago\nFINAL COTTON REPORT\n11261163 Bales Were Ginned From\nCotton Croppf 1907\nSpecial to the Herald\nWashington D C March 20 The\ncensus bureau reports that 112G11C3\nbales of cotton were ginned by 27577\nSinners of the 1907 crop\nINVITATION ACCEPTED\nBig American Battleship Fleet Will\nVisit a Japanese Port During\nTrip Around the World\nSpecial to the Herald\nWashington D C March 20 The\nmikado of Japan has extended a per\nsonal invitation for the American bat\ntleship fleet to visit one of the Jap\nanese ports on Its trip around the\nworld A cablnent meeting today will\nconsider the invitation\nInvitation Accepted\nSpecial to the Herald\nWashington D C March 20 The\ncabinet meeting decided to accept Ja\npans Invitation for the American fleet\nto visit a Japanese port on the squad\nrons trip around the world\nBishop Fowler Dead\nSpecial to the Herald\nNew York March 20 Bishop Chas\nHenry Fowler of the Methodist church\ndied at his home here today Death\nfollowed an operation for diabetes\nthe shock killing the bishop\nJas F Brook architect and engl\nIneer Room 7 Link building tf\nmS\n15 CTS A WEEK\nThat Advertiser Gets Most From His Advertising Who Sayf Just What He Can Do and Does Just What He Says\nJno R Hbabnb President\nTHE\nTuokeb Botall Cashier\nRoyall National BanK\nPALESTINE TEXAS\nCapital SIOOOOOOO Surplus and Profits S64I0793\nStatement at the close of business Feb 14th 1908\nRESOURCES\nLoans and Discounts t2S712l 22\nU 8 Bonds and Premiums 2625000\nBanking House and Fixtures 2000000\nCash J U00S105\nTotal\n1153 455 27\nCapital Stool\nSurplus and Profits\nCirculation\nBills Payable\nDeposits\nTotal\nLIABILITIES\n10000000\n64 10793\n25000X0\n1EK800\n215811 34\nH53455 27\nEvery Stetson bears the\nStetson Nome\nStetson\nHat\nIts the man who looks into\nthings carefully the man who is\nparticular who always insists\nupon the Stetson\nWe have the Stetson Soft and Derby\nHats in all the latest styles\nW B Flanagan\nF\nL\nUndertaking\nAND\nEmbalming\nfS WA NN\nFurniture and\nCarpet Co\nAn Invitation\nShould you desire to inform your\nself fully in regard to the appro\npriate spring styles if you wish\nto see and compare as many as\npossible of the different models\nbefore buying one we extend to\nyou a special invitation to visit\nour store and permit us to place\nbefore you the large variety and\nselection we havesecured and\nare showing this season\nStylish Suits 16 50\nand up\nJ\nDOYLE BROTHERS\nTAILORS\nJ\ni\nu","height":"26856","width":"18144"}}
